# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 JavaScript Extension Architecture (Block-Level Functional Architecture Flow)

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    CoreJS["Core JavaScript ES5"] --> ES6["ES6+ Language Features let const arrow template destructuring spread rest classes modules"]
    CoreJS --> Promises["Promises and async await"]
    CoreJS --> JSONCore["JSON Object Notation"]
    CoreJS --> XHR["XMLHttpRequest XHR Object"]

    ES6 --> DevExp["Improved Developer Experience"]

    Promises --> AsyncPattern["Asynchronous Pattern"]
    XHR --> AsyncPattern
    FetchAPI["Fetch API Promise Based"] --> AsyncPattern

    AsyncPattern --> AJAX["AJAX Technique No Page Reload"]

    JSONCore --> DataInterchange["Data Interchange Format"]
    AJAX --> WebApp["Modern Web Application SPA REST APIs"]
    DevExp --> WebApp
    DataInterchange --> WebApp

    WebApp --> User["End User Dynamic UI Fast Response"]
```

## 4.2 Promise State Transition Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> pending
    pending --> fulfilled: resolve value called
    pending --> rejected: reject reason called
    fulfilled --> [*]: immutable settled
    rejected --> [*]: immutable settled

    note right of pending: Initial state Async operation in progress
    note right of fulfilled: Success Has a value then handlers fire
    note right of rejected: Failure Has an error catch handlers fire
```

## 4.3 AJAX Request-Response Cycle

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User Browser
    participant JS as JavaScript Engine
    participant X as XHR or Fetch
    participant S as Web Server
    participant DB as Database

    U->>JS: Trigger event click submit
    JS->>X: xhr.open or fetch URL
    X->>S: HTTP Request GET POST
    S->>DB: Query data
    DB-->>S: Return rows
    S-->>X: HTTP Response status 200 JSON or XML
    X-->>JS: onload or await response
    JS->>U: Update DOM innerHTML
    Note over U,DB: NO full page reload only specific UI section updated
```

