### Question A2 — `[KTU University Exam - May 2024]`

**Q: What is AJAX? List any four advantages of using AJAX in web applications.**

**Model Answer:**

> [!NOTE]
> **AJAX (Asynchronous JavaScript and XML)** is a web development technique used to send and receive data from a server **asynchronously** without requiring a full page reload. It uses `XMLHttpRequest` (or the modern `Fetch API`) to communicate with the server in the background.

**Four Advantages of AJAX:**

1. **Improved User Experience** — Only specific sections of the page are updated; the user does not experience a "flash" of a blank page.
2. **Reduced Bandwidth Usage** — Only the necessary data (JSON/XML) is exchanged, not the entire HTML page.
3. **Faster Response Time** — Asynchronous calls allow the user to continue interacting with the page while data loads in the background.
4. **Better Interactivity** — Enables features like **live search**, **autocomplete**, **infinite scroll**, and **real-time chat** (e.g., Gmail, Google Maps).

**Additional advantages (for bonus marks):**
- Separation of concerns (data layer vs presentation layer).
- Supports RESTful API integration.
- Reduces server load (no full-page processing required).

