## 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

### 4.1 Control Flow Diagram — `if` Statement

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A([Start]) --> B[Evaluate Condition C]
    B --> C{Is C TRUE?}
    C -- Yes --> D[Execute Block A]
    C -- No --> E[Skip Block A]
    D --> F([Continue Program])
    E --> F
```

### 4.2 Control Flow Diagram — `if...else` Statement

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A([Start]) --> B[Evaluate Condition C]
    B --> C{Is C TRUE?}
    C -- Yes --> D[Execute TRUE Block]
    C -- No --> E[Execute FALSE Block]
    D --> F([Continue Program])
    E --> F
```

### 4.3 Control Flow Diagram — `if...else if...else` Ladder

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A([Start]) --> B[Evaluate Condition 1]
    B --> C{Is C1 TRUE?}
    C -- Yes --> D[Execute Block 1]
    C -- No --> E[Evaluate Condition 2]
    E --> F{Is C2 TRUE?}
    F -- Yes --> G[Execute Block 2]
    F -- No --> H[Execute Default Block]
    D --> I([Continue Program])
    G --> I
    H --> I
```

### 4.4 Control Flow Diagram — `switch` Statement (with Fall-Through)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A([Start]) --> B[Evaluate Switch Expression E]
    B --> C{Case 1 match?}
    C -- Yes --> D[Execute Case 1 Code]
    C -- No --> E{Case 2 match?}
    E -- Yes --> F[Execute Case 2 Code]
    F --> G{break statement?}
    G -- Yes --> K([Exit Switch])
    G -- No --> H[Fall Through to Case 3]
    E -- No --> I{Case 3 match?}
    I -- Yes --> J[Execute Case 3 Code]
    I -- No --> L[Execute Default Block]
    D --> K
    H --> I
    J --> K
    L --> K
```

