#### ✅ Model Solution

**Part (a) — Forms of `if` Statements:**

1. **Simple `if`**
    ```javascript
    if (x > 0) {
        console.log("Positive");
    }
    ```

2. **`if...else`**
    ```javascript
    if (x % 2 === 0) {
        console.log("Even");
    } else {
        console.log("Odd");
    }
    ```

3. **`if...else if...else` Ladder**
    ```javascript
    if (x > 0)      console.log("Positive");
    else if (x < 0) console.log("Negative");
    else            console.log("Zero");
    ```

4. **Nested `if`**
    ```javascript
    if (x > 0) {
        if (x % 2 === 0) {
            console.log("Positive Even");
        }
    }
    ```

**Part (b) — Grade Assignment Program:**

```javascript
let marks = 78;
let grade;

if (marks < 0 || marks > 100) {
    console.log("Invalid marks! Please enter a value between 0 and 100.");
} else if (marks >= 90) {
    grade = "A";
    console.log("Grade: " + grade + " (Excellent)");
} else if (marks >= 75) {
    grade = "B";
    console.log("Grade: " + grade + " (Very Good)");
} else if (marks >= 60) {
    grade = "C";
    console.log("Grade: " + grade + " (Good)");
} else if (marks >= 40) {
    grade = "D";
    console.log("Grade: " + grade + " (Pass)");
} else {
    grade = "F";
    console.log("Grade: " + grade + " (Fail)");
}
```

**Trace for `marks = 78`:**
1. `marks < 0 || marks > 100` → $78 < 0$ is false, $78 > 100$ is false → overall `false`. Skip.
2. `marks >= 90` → $78 \geq 90$ → `false`. Skip.
3. `marks >= 75` → $78 \geq 75$ → **`true`**. Execute this block.
4. Output: `Grade: B (Very Good)`.

